  "doc_id": "11908",
  "text": "Pain has a multidimensional nature, and its presentation varies according to the structure affected and the type of associated dysfunction patterns [CITATION_1] . According to the International Association for the Study of Pain (IASP-1994), an individual learns the meaning of the word \"pain\" through experiences related to injuries from the beginning of life, thus the experience of pain is always personal and carries subjectivity. Chronic pain is defined as that with no apparent neuropathic or nociceptive damage or dysfunction, but persists beyond the normal time required for tissue healing, bringing challenge to generate satisfactory outcomes through pharmacological and non-pharmacological treatments [CITATION_2] .",
